[h1]BioShock Infinite[/h1]

[u]Verdict[/u]: the amount of positive reviews speaks for itself—this is a great story-driven game with some solid gameplay. It ties the trilogy together perfectly with a narrative that is enough in itself to increase replay value. Infinite is a thoroughly fulfilling and thought-provoking experience that boasts a lot of well-executed ideas and a lot of heart. If you experience any technical difficulties, [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=203916658]these tips[/url] helped me out quite a bit.

[b]Pros:[/b]
[list]
[*]Great retro sci-fi world, always changing and in motion;
[*]Courageous, thought-provoking story with a brilliant ending;
[*]Fittingly flawed characters and warring philosophies;
[*]Protagonist with his own personality that actually speaks (as opposed to Jack, Delta and Sigma so far);
[*]Decent graphics (if a bit inconsistent) and beautiful art style;
[*]Tight gameplay enhanced by your companion;
[*]Some worthwhile collectibles add to the rich lore;
[*]Great replay value thanks to complex but intriguing narrative;
[*]Brilliant DLC adds a lot to the main narrative and reimagines gameplay elements.
[/list]
[b]Cons:[/b]
[list]
[*]A few minor annoyance with prompts (e.g. when trying to grab a slightly out of reach object);
[*]Some collectibles are just busywork;
[*]Checkpoints can feel few and far between.
[/list]
